abstract: The bride and groom, who each graduated from Pitt, met in December 2010 on a blind date arranged by a mutual friend.
snippet: The bride and groom, who each graduated from Pitt, met in December 2010 on a blind date arranged by a mutual friend.
lead_paragraph: Heather Anne Chronis and Michael Vincent Danek were married April 6. The Rev. Brian Bennett, a Lutheran minister, performed the ceremony at the Heinz Memorial Chapel on the campus of the University of Pittsburgh.

abstract: All of the weddings right here on one handy page for you.
snippet: All of the weddings right here on one handy page for you.
lead_paragraph: Lauren Jade Attaway and Rogelio Isaac Thomas Jr. were married April 6 at University United Methodist Church in Indianapolis. The Rev. Dr. L. Wayne Smith, a pastor at the church, performed the ceremony.

headline_main: Robert B. Reich’s Recipe for a Just Society

abstract: For years, employees complained about the behavior of the head of the division, Kevin Carwile, and what they viewed as a toxic culture.
snippet: For years, employees complained about the behavior of the head of the division, Kevin Carwile, and what they viewed as a toxic culture.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When Kevin Carwile arrived to run the Justice Department’s death penalty unit in 2010, he had never prosecuted or sat through an entire capital punishment case. He was moved into the job after overseeing the gangs unit, and some prosecutors worried he lacked the expertise to steer the division.

abstract: Even though Mr. Trump still takes potshots at Amazon, the industry’s relationship with the White House is shifting as tech companies find some common ground with the president.
snippet: Even though Mr. Trump still takes potshots at Amazon, the industry’s relationship with the White House is shifting as tech companies find some common ground with the president.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Two days after Donald J. Trump won the 2016 election, executives at Google consoled their employees in an all-staff meeting broadcast around the world.

abstract: The defensive end for the Philadelphia Eagles is accused of injuring an elderly woman while trying to get on the field after Super Bowl LI in 2017.
snippet: The defensive end for the Philadelphia Eagles is accused of injuring an elderly woman while trying to get on the field after Super Bowl LI in 2017.
lead_paragraph: Michael Bennett, the Pro Bowl defensive end who recently was traded to the Philadelphia Eagles, surrendered to the authorities in Houston on Monday on a charge that he injured a woman in a wheelchair while trying to get onto the field after Super Bowl LI.
